South Korean Agency Tenders to Buy 3,000 Tons of Aluminum

-- B y   S u n g w o o   P a r k
-- 
2011-05-19T02:25:05Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-19/south-korean-agency-tenders-to-buy-3-000-tons-of-aluminum-1-.html
South Korea ,  Asia ’s third-biggest
buyer of base metals, plans to buy 3,000 metric tons of high
grade, primary aluminum for shipment by July 20 through tenders
next week, according to a state agency.  The Public Procurement Service, a state-run body that
manages strategic commodities, is seeking to purchase 2,000 tons
in a May 25 tender, according to a notice on the Service’s
website. The agency will buy the remainder in bidding scheduled
for May 26, another notice showed.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sungwoo Park in Seoul at 
 spark47@bloomberg.ne   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
